paragraphs.text:
%neo4j_algo
CALL algo.labelPropagation.stream("Library", "DEPENDS_ON",
  { iterations: 10 })
YIELD nodeId, label
RETURN label,
       collect(algo.getNodeById(nodeId).id) AS libraries
ORDER BY size(libraries) DESC

paragraphs.text:
%md

We can also run the algorithm assuming that the graph is undirected, which means
that nodes will try to adopt labels from the libraries they depend on as well as ones
that depend on them.

To do this, we pass the DIRECTION:BOTH parameter to the algorithm:

that nodes will try to adopt labels from the libraries they depend on as well as ones

To do this, we pass the DIRECTION:BOTH parameter to the algorithm:

paragraphs.text:
%neo4j_algo
CALL algo.labelPropagation.stream("Library", "DEPENDS_ON",
{ iterations: 10, direction: "BOTH" })
YIELD nodeId, label
RETURN label,
collect(algo.getNodeById(nodeId).id) AS libraries
ORDER BY size(libraries) DESC

Preferred way to use GDS library is with loaded named graphs, where we first load the graph into memory and then proceed to run algorithms on it.
We can load both the directed and undirected projection of the relationships in a single named graph.
